
USAGE
        TAlk <user> <message>

DESCRIPTION
        Sends a one-line message to another user of the node. 
        The user must be in idle state (ie. not connected/connecting or running a program).

        If the user has an SSID other than zero, the SSID must be used.
        All users who are logged in with the same callsign-ssid and in an idle state will receive the message.

EXAMPLE
        talk oh7lzb-3 Good evening, Hessu!
